      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The MACRS formula for depreciation on a piece of heavy equipment like an industrial excavator is a bit complex, but I'll break it down for you. The MACRS (Modified Accelerated Cost Recovery System) formula is a tax deduction method that allows businesses to depreciate assets over their useful life. For an industrial excavator purchased in 2023, it falls under the 5-year or 7-year asset class, depending on its intended use.\n\nTo calculate the MACRS depreciation, you'll need to know the asset's cost, its useful life, and the recovery period. The 5-year recovery period applies to most heavy equipment, including excavators, while the 7-year recovery period is typically used for longer-lived assets, like industrial machinery. \n\nFor the 5-year recovery period, the MACRS formula is:\n\nYear 1: 100% x (1 - (1 / 5))\nYear 2: 100% x (1 - (1 / 5)) x (1 - (1 / 5))\nYear 3: 100% x (1 - (1 / 5)) x (1 - (1 / 5)) x (1 - (1 / 5))\nYear",
